## 3. {{SKILLS}} — repeatable workflows

*{{EPI_SKILLS}}*

A {{SKILL}} is a written procedure for a recurring task. Run the matching {{SKILL}}
before improvising. Specs live in [`{{DIR_SKILLS}}/`]({{DIR_SKILLS}}/).

| {{SKILL}} | Trigger |
| --- | --- |
| [brainstorm]({{DIR_SKILLS}}/brainstorm.md) | a new feature or design with no plan yet |
| [plan]({{DIR_SKILLS}}/plan.md) | a task has more than a couple of steps |
| [parallel-agents]({{DIR_SKILLS}}/parallel-agents.md) | several independent subtasks and a tool that runs subagents |
| [cmux]({{DIR_SKILLS}}/cmux.md) | running subagents inside cmux and you want to watch each one live in its own pane |
| [tdd]({{DIR_SKILLS}}/tdd.md) | implementing behaviour that can be pinned by a test |
| [verify]({{DIR_SKILLS}}/verify.md) | about to claim something is done |
| [debug]({{DIR_SKILLS}}/debug.md) | a bug or failure to diagnose before fixing |
| [repo-map]({{DIR_SKILLS}}/repo-map.md) | orienting to the repo, or structure changed |
| [ingest]({{DIR_SKILLS}}/ingest.md) | a task needs content from a PDF, Office doc, or URL |
| [commit]({{DIR_SKILLS}}/commit.md) | staging and writing a commit |
| [code-review]({{DIR_SKILLS}}/code-review.md) | reviewing a diff or PR |
| [ship]({{DIR_SKILLS}}/ship.md) | a verified change is ready to open as a PR or merge |
| [release]({{DIR_SKILLS}}/release.md) | cutting a version: bump, changelog, tag |
| [refactor]({{DIR_SKILLS}}/refactor.md) | improving code structure without changing behaviour |
| [handoff]({{DIR_SKILLS}}/handoff.md) | context filling, or passing work to another agent or session |
| [roast-me]({{DIR_SKILLS}}/roast-me.md) | you want an artifact torn apart, brutally and actionably |
| [create-skill]({{DIR_SKILLS}}/create-skill.md) | a task has crystallised into a repeatable pattern |

When a task repeats and no {{SKILL}} covers it, forge one (see `create-skill`).

